{
  "stem": "95.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They were all maybe in the middle-- their late teens-- 18, 19, 20 years old, 22 years old.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And remarkably, these-- all these young ladies at the end of, like, '38, '39, went to Israel, to Palestine, and stayed there.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We had [INAUDIBLE]-- we had one woman who I still didn't get in contact with.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We always knew her as Lou.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And Lou immigrated to Palestine in 1939.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Her name-- I never knew her last name.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And then I find out her name was Lou Cadard, and Lou Cadard in Israel became Golda Meir's private secretary and companion until Golda Meir died.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I'm going way ahead of my time, but I saw Lou the last time in 1938 or '39.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Then I went to the World Gathering of the Jewish Survivors of the Holocaust in 1981, in Israel, and there I saw Lou again.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And she said to me, I don't want you to look at me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I'm old and ugly.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I said, well, I'm old, but pretty.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "[LAUGHTER] It was a really-- because she was such a remarkable woman, it was such a thrill to see her after all these years.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "She was-- they were great ladies.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "They would take care of us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "They would teach us the Bible.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "They would we see to it that we will become good human beings.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Not only our parents were decent people, most of them, but they helped us to really have a great life.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I think about it-- why did I survive the Holocaust?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Why me except for a lot of people?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think what helped me tremendously-- it's my background.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
